
Ranger Help for: setenemy
=========================

SYNTAX:      setenemy/setenemy <race here>
USAGE:       Any wilderness terrain.

SUMMARY:    
Setenemy allows a Ranger to set his or her enemy species. What races a
Ranger can set is based on his or her primary terrain, so it must be set
first. You can type just setenemy with no argument to see a list of
allowable races. Keep in mind that your follower cannot be of the same race
as your enemy species. So if you like horses, don't choose horse as your
enemy species.

Use 'rhelp <species>' or 'rhelp enemy <species>' before choosing. For
example: 'rhelp bear', 'rhelp enemy dragon', or 'rhelp lycanthrope'.

Changing your enemy species later requires Warden Thorn's reattunement
ritual. Use 'rhelp reattune' for details.

